* [[tänkbarhet]]

====Usage notes====
Regarding the sense of ''to intend'' or ''to mean'', '''tänka''' is the main option signifying a setup plan, while ''[[mena]]'' (somewhat more colloquial) signifies what are the immediate consequences. For example: ''I didn't mean to knock your tooth out'' = ''Jag '''menade''' inte att slå ut dina tänder''. Here, a translation with "tänka" (''Jag '''tänkte''' inte...'') may give the impression of ''I didn't make any explicit plans to knock your teeth out''

